Other features of the invention include, as examples only:
A. A mechanized system for sterilizing products comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel having one or more sidewalls, an entrance and an exit, said tunnel subdivided into a plurality of consecutively aligned stages including at least a heating stage and a cooling stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of at least one of said stages;
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage and separate at least one stage from an adjacent stage;
a heating means for providing heating in at least one stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including a series of magnetrons for creating a microwave field for heating products;
a conveyor for transporting products from upline to downline through said conditioning unit;
said conveyor means including a motor positioned exterior of said tunnel, a plurality of wheels located within said tunnel, a plurality of shafts mechanically connected to said motor and said wheels, said shafts projecting through holes formed in said tunnel sidewalls to engage said wheels,
activation of said motor causing corresponding rotation of said shafts and said wheels.
B. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of A wherein said conveyor does not include a conveyor belt or rollers projecting laterally across the interior of said tunnel.
C. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of B wherein said tunnel includes at least four stages including a preheating stage, a heating stage, a holding stage and a cooling stage, each of said stages including a plurality of wheels located within said stages, said wheels connected to said motor by shafts which project through holes formed in said tunnel sidewalls of said stages.
D. A conditioning system for sterilizing products comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel having parallel top wall and bottom wall, parallel sidewalls, and an entrance and an exit to form a conduit having a substantially quadrilateral cross-section, said tunnel subdivided into a plurality of consecutively aligned stages including at least a heating stage and a cooling stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of at least one of said stages;
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage and separate at least one stage from an adjacent stage;
a heating means for providing heating in at least one stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including a series of magnetrons for creating a microwave field for heating products; and
a conveyor for transporting products from upline to downline through said conditioning unit.
E. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of D wherein each of said stages has opposing parallel top and bottom walls and opposing parallel sidewalls so that said tunnel has a substantially rectangular cross section.
F. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of E wherein said tunnel includes at least four stages including a preheating stage, a heating stage, a holding stage and a cooling stage.
G. A conditioning system for sterilizing products comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel having one or more sidewalls, an entrance and an exit, said tunnel subdivided into a plurality of consecutively aligned stages including at least a heating stage and a cooling stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of at least one of said stages;
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage and separate at least one stage from an adjacent stage;
a heating means for providing heating in at least one stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including a series of magnetrons for creating a microwave field for heating products;
a conveyor for transporting products from upline to downline through said conditioning unit;
said tunnel including at least one inlet projecting through one of said sidewalls and an outlet projecting through one of said sidewalls, said inlet connected to a pressurized source of cleaning fluid for introducing cleaning fluid from the exterior of said tunnel into the interior of said tunnel, said outlet allowing cleaning fluid to drain from said tunnel.
H. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of G wherein each of said stages has opposing parallel top and bottom walls and opposing parallel sidewalls so that said tunnel has a substantially rectangular cross section.
I. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of H wherein said tunnel includes at least four stages including a preheating stage, a heating stage, a holding stage and a cooling stage.
J. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of I wherein each stage includes an inlet for introducing cleaning fluid from the exterior of said tunnel into the interior of said stage and an outlet allowing cleaning fluid to drain from said stage.
K. A conditioning system for sterilizing products comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel having one or more sidewalls, an entrance and an exit, said tunnel subdivided into a plurality of consecutively aligned stages including at least a heating stage and a cooling stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of at least one of said stages;
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage and separate at least one stage from an adjacent stage;
a heating means for providing heating in at least one stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including a series of magnetrons for creating a microwave field for heating products;
a conveyor for transporting products from upline to downline through said conditioning unit, or from dowuline to upline through said conditioning unit;
a temperature sensor for measuring the temperature of products traveling through said tunnel; and
a controller connected to said conveyor and said temperature sensor; said controller controlling said conveyor to move products upline or dowuline depending on temperature measurements of the products within the tunnel.
L. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of K wherein each of said stages has opposing parallel top and bottom walls and opposing parallel sidewalls so that said tunnel has a substantially rectangular cross section.
M. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of L wherein said tunnel includes at least four stages including a preheating stage, a heating stage, a holding stage and a cooling stage.
N. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of M wherein each stage includes an inlet for introducing cleaning fluid from the exterior of said tunnel into the interior of said stage and an outlet allowing cleaning fluid to drain from said stage.
O. A conditioning system for sterilizing products comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel having one or more sidewalls, an entrance and an exit, said tunnel subdivided into a plurality of consecutively aligned stages including at least a heating stage and a cooling stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of at least one of said stages;
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage and separate at least one stage from an adjacent stage;
a heating means for providing heating in at least one stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including a series of magnetrons for creating a microwave field for heating products, said magnetrons being controllable to controllably alter said microwave field within said stage;
a conveyor for transporting products from upline to downline through said conditioning unit;
a temperature sensor for measuring the temperature of products traveling through said tunnel; and
a controller connected to said heating means and said temperature sensor; said controller controlling said magnetrons to alter said microwave field within said stage depending on temperature measurements of the products within the tunnel.
P. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of 0 wherein said magnetrons produce a controllably moveable microwave field and said controller controlling said magnetrons to move said microwave field within said stage depending on temperature measurements of the products within the tunnel.
Q. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of O wherein said conveyor moves said products upline to downline or downline to upline through said tunnel and said conveyor is connected to said controller, said controller controlling said conveyor to move products upline or downline depending on temperature measurements of the products within the tunnel.
R. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of Q wherein said tunnel includes at least four stages including a preheating stage, a heating stage, a holding stage and a cooling stage.
S. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of P wherein each of said stages has opposing parallel top and bottom walls and opposing parallel sidewalls so that said tunnel has a substantially rectangular cross section.
T. The conditioning system for sterilizing products of O wherein each stage includes an inlet for introducing cleaning fluid from the exterior of said tunnel into the interior of said stage and an outlet allowing cleaning fluid to drain from said stage.

claim.claim-text:
Aufbereitungssystem zur Sterilisierung von Produkten in versiegelten Packungen (1), beinhaltend:
eine Produktaufbereitungseinheit, die einen Tunnel (A) mit zwei Paaren paralleler Seitenwände und einen Eingang und einen Ausgang aufweist, um eine Rohrleitung zu bilden, die im Wesentlichen einen vierseitigen Querschnitt aufweist, wobei der Tunnel (A) in eine oder mehrere aufeinanderfolgend ausgerichtete Stufen (A1, A2, A3, A4) unterteilt ist;
eine Vielzahl von Druck abdichtenden Türen, um zumindest eine Stufe abzudichten, um eine gasdichte unter Druck setzbare Stufe zu bilden;
ein Druckbeaufschlagungsmittel zur Steuerung des Drucks der unter Druck setzbaren Stufe und zur Erhöhung des Drucks innerhalb der unter Druck setzbaren Stufe auf einen ausreichenden Pegel, um zu verhindern, dass die versiegelten Packungen (1) nach Aufbringen von Wärme bersten;
ein Fördereinrichtungsmittel zum Vorrücken von Produkten von stromaufwärts nach stromabwärts durch die Aufbereitungseinheit; und
ein Heizungsmittel zum Bereitstellen von Wärme in zumindest der unter Druck setzbaren Stufe der Aufbereitungseinheit, wobei das Heizungsmittel erste und zweite Sätze von Mikrowellenquellen zur Schaffung eines Mikrowellenfelds zum Erwärmen von Produkten einschließt, wobei der erste Satz von Mikrowellenquellen eine oder mehr Mikrowellenquellen einschließt, die Mikrowellen in einem rechten Winkel zur Vorrückachse von Produkten emittieren, die durch den Tunnel vorrücken und der zweite Satz von Mikrowellenquellen eine oder mehr Mikrowellenquellen einschließt, die Mikrowellen in einem rechten Winkel zur Vorrückachse von Produkten emittieren, die durch den Tunnel vorrücken, wobei der erste Satz von Mikrowellenquellen direkt mit einer ersten Seitenwand verbunden ist und der zweite Satz von Mikrowellenquellen direkt mit einer zweiten gegenüberliegenden Seitenwand verbunden ist, sodass Mikrowellenenergie von den ersten Mikrowellenquellen ab einer ersten Seite der Produkte ausstrahlt und Mikrowellenenergie von den zweiten Mikrowellenquellen ab einer gegenüberliegenden Seite der Produkte ausstrahlt.

A conditioning system for sterilizing products within sealed packages (1) comprising:
a product conditioning unit including of a tunnel (A) having two pairs of parallel sidewalls, and an entrance and an exit to form a conduit having a substantially quadrilateral cross-section, said tunnel (A) subdivided into one or more consecutively aligned stages; (A1, A2, A3, A4)
a plurality of pressure sealing doors to seal at least one stage to form a gaseous tight sealed pressurizeable stage;
a pressurizing means for controlling the pressure of said pressurizeable stage and for increasing the pressure within said pressurizeable stage to a sufficient level to prevent sealed packages (1) from bursting upon application of heat;
a conveyor means for advancing products from up line to downline through said conditioning unit; and
a heating means for providing heating in at least said pressurizeable stage of the conditioning unit, said heating means including first and second sets of microwave sources for creating a microwave field for heating products wherein said first set of microwave sources includes one or more microwave sources which emit microwaves at a right angle to the axis of advance of products advancing through said tunnel and said second set of microwave sources includes one or more microwave sources which emit microwaves at a right angle to the axis of advance of products advancing through said tunnel, said first set of microwave sources directly connected to a first sidewall and said second set of microwave sources directly connected to a second opposing sidewall so that microwave energy emanates from said first microwave sources from a first side of said products and microwave energy emanates from said second microwave sources from an opposite side of said products.

Système de conditionnement pour la stérilisation de produits dans des emballages étanches (1) comprenant:
une unité de conditionnement de produits y compris un tunnel (A) comportant deux paires de parois latérales parallèles, ainsi qu'un point d'entrée et un point de sortie, le tout constituant un conduit dont la coupe transversale est essentiellement en forme de quadrilatère, le tunnel (A) étant subdivisé en un seul ou en plusieurs étages consécutivement alignés (A1, A2, A3, A4);
une pluralité de portes à garniture d'étanchéité servant à rendre étanche au moins l'un des étages afin de former un étage pressurisable étanche au gaz;
un moyen de pressurisation servant à contrôler la pression de l'étage pressurisable et à augmenter la pression à l'intérieur de cet étage pressurisable jusqu'à un niveau suffisant pour empêcher l'éclatement des emballages étanches (1) lorsque la chaleur est appliquée;
un transporteur servant à faire avancer les produits d'amont en aval à travers l'unité de conditionnement;
un moyen de chauffage servant à chauffer au moins l'étage pressurisable de l'unité de conditionnement, ce moyen de chauffage comportant un premier et un deuxième ensembles de sources de chauffage aux micro-ondes qui créent un champ de micro-ondes utilisées pour chauffer les produits, caractérisé en ce que le premier ensemble de sources aux micro-ondes comprend une ou plusieurs sources de micro-ondes qui transmettent les micro-ondes à angle droit par rapport à l'axe d'avancement des produits qui passent à travers le tunnel, et en ce que le deuxième ensemble de sources aux micro-ondes comprend une ou plusieurs sources de micro-ondes qui transmettent les micro-ondes à angle droit par rapport à l'axe d'avancement des produits qui passent à travers le tunnel, le premier ensemble de sources aux micro-ondes étant directement raccordé à une prermière paroi latérale, et le deuxième ensemble de sources aux micro-ondes étant directement raccordé à une deuxième paroi latérale opposée, de sorte que l'énergie des micro-ondes provient des premières sources aux micro-ondes à partir d'un premier côté des produits et l'énergie des micro-ondes provient des deuxièmes sources aux micro-ondes à partir du côté opposé de ces produits.
